-- Deutsche Bank to Revamp Strategy Unit, Handelsblatt Says
-- B y   N i c h o l a s   C o m f o r t
-- 2012-03-29T16:31:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-29/deutsche-bank-to-revamp-strategy-unit-handelsblatt-says.html
Deutsche Bank AG (DBK) ’s designated co-
Chief Executive Officers Anshu Jain and Juergen Fitschen plan to
reorganize the bank’s group strategy and planning department,
Handelsblatt reported in an e-mailed summary of an article.  The division will report on matters of strategy to Henry Ritchotte, who will take over as the Frankfurt-based bank’s
chief operating officer in June, the newspaper said, citing
unidentified people close to the financial industry.  Chief Financial Officer  Stefan Krause  will be responsible
for the department’s planning operations and the sale of assets
in the corporate investments division, Handelsblatt said, citing
an unidentified person familiar with the matter.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nicholas Comfort in Frankfurt at 
